    "text": "When we change the parameters that determine $f_{1}$ , all of the derivatives in this sequence are evaluated at slightly different locations since layers $f_{2}$ , $f_{3}$ , and $f_{4}$ are themselves computed from $f_{1}$ . Consequently, the updated gradient at each training example may be completely different, and the loss function becomes badly behaved. [^1]",
